  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And there went out after him Joab's men,.... Who though he was removed from his post as general, yet might still have the command of a regiment: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Cherethites, and the Pelethites; over whom Benaiah was, 2 Samuel 20:23; these attended David in his flight, and had now returned with him, 2 Samuel 15:18, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and the Cherethites, and the Pelethites; over whom Benaiah was, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 20:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; these attended David in his flight, and had now returned with him, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 15:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all the mighty men; the military men that were at Jerusalem as many as could be spared: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they went out of Jerusalem to pursue after Sheba the son of Bichri; with Abishai at the head of them; Josephus (q) says there were six hundred, besides the soldiers at Jerusalem that went on this pursuit. ",
        "children": []
